# Code Owners

This file defines who owns which parts of the repository. Code owners are automatically requested for review when pull requests are opened.

## Repository Owners

* @maskom-team

## Core Application

All files in the main application (root directory) are owned by the core team:

```
* @maskom-team
```

## Legacy Application

The legacy `web-sch-12/` directory is deprecated and changes should be minimal:

```
/web-sch-12/ @maskom-team
```

## Configuration and Infrastructure

Critical configuration and infrastructure files:

```
/.github/ @maskom-team
/composer.json @maskom-team
/frontend/package.json @maskom-team
/.env.example @maskom-team
/docker-compose.yml @maskom-team
```

## Security and Compliance

Security-related files and documentation:

```
/SECURITY.md @maskom-team
/CONTRIBUTING.md @maskom-team
/LICENSE @maskom-team
```

## Documentation

Project documentation:

```
/README.md @maskom-team
/docs/ @maskom-team
*.md @maskom-team
```

## Review Requirements

- **All PRs** require approval from at least one code owner
- **Security-related changes** require approval from core team
- **Breaking changes** require approval from core team
- **Database migrations** require approval from core team

## Emergency Changes

For critical security fixes, the core team can bypass normal review processes and merge directly to the main branch.

## Questions

If you're unsure who should review your changes, tag `@maskom-team` and we will help route your PR to the right reviewers.